text: The Papyrus Schøyen MS 2648 (also Rahlfs 816, P. Schoyen. 1 23, TM 66869, LDAB 8119) are six leaves of a papyrus codex of the Septuagint that contain the text of Joshua 9:27-11:3 in Koine Greek. By comparative writing styles (palaeography), it has been dated to the early third century (from about 200/215 CE). == References == == Sources == * * * * * * * * Category:3rd- century biblical manuscripts Category:Septuagint manuscripts
title: Papyrus Schøyen 2648
